race.comment: OFF THE PRESS (7) made it two from two this prep when he came from a long way back to score over 1200m at Wagga Riverside last start. Up in grade this time but he drops 4kgs with the claim and draws perfectly. Can compete at this level. MAFIA (2) has raced well all prep but a win has been elusive. Raced on the pace but was overwhelmed late and finished midfield in a 1200m Randwick Highway last time out. Races well here and from a good gate will be given every chance by Berry. HEURISTIC (3) was prominent from the outset and looked a chance at the furlong until the heavy supported Carbonados overpowered him in the closing stages over 1200m at Randwick on Big Dance Day. Very fit now and gets his chance to break a long win drought. FLIGHTCREW (5) was edged out by Taxation over 1100m at Rosehill recently. Improvement to come at just the third run of the campaign. NEW BUSINESS (4) might need one more run but is not out of contention.
